## Plan: Add `mistral-instruct-v3` Specialized Chat Template Handler

After thoroughly exploring the codebase, here is my complete implementation plan. **Only `common/chat.cpp` needs to be modified** — no changes to `common/chat.h`.

---

### Edit 1 — New handler function
**Location**: Insert after line 1517 (end of `common_chat_params_init_gigachat_v3`), before `namespace workaround {`

```cpp
static common_chat_params common_chat_params_init_mistral_instruct_v3(
        const common_chat_template & tmpl,
        const autoparser::generation_params & inputs) {

    common_chat_params data;

    std::string system_content;
    bool first_user = true;

    data.prompt = tmpl.bos_token();

    for (const auto & msg : inputs.messages) {
        auto role    = msg.value("role", "");
        auto content = msg.value("content", "");

        if (role == "system") {
            system_content = content;
        } else if (role == "user") {
            if (first_user && !system_content.empty()) {
                data.prompt += "[INST] " + system_content + "\n" + content + " [/INST]";
            } else {
                data.prompt += "[INST] " + content + " [/INST]";
            }
            first_user = false;
        } else if (role == "assistant") {
            data.prompt += " " + content + "</s>";
        }
    }

    data.format = COMMON_CHAT_FORMAT_CONTENT_ONLY;
    return data;
}
```

This produces exactly:
- With system: `<s>[INST] system\nuser1 [/INST] assistant1</s>[INST] user2 [/INST]`
- Without system: `<s>[INST] user1 [/INST] assistant1</s>[INST] user2 [/INST]`

