### Edit 2 — Detection block
**Location**: Inside `common_chat_try_specialized_template()`, after the GigaChatV3 block (~line 1688), before `return std::nullopt`

```cpp
    // Mistral Instruct v0.3 - uses [INST]/[/INST] markers without [SYSTEM_PROMPT]
    if (src.find("[INST]") != std::string::npos &&
        src.find("[/INST]") != std::string::npos &&
        src.find("[SYSTEM_PROMPT]") == std::string::npos) {
        LOG_DBG("Using specialized template: Mistral Instruct v3\n");
        return common_chat_params_init_mistral_instruct_v3(tmpl, params);
    }
```

The `[SYSTEM_PROMPT]` negative check prevents any collision with the Ministral 3 handler (which detects `[SYSTEM_PROMPT]` and runs earlier in the chain anyway).
